11 (iii) pay to the Commission an application fee set by the Commission;
12 (iv) 1. if the applicant is a Maryland driver, allow the
13 Commission access to the driver’s photograph through the Motor Vehicle Administration;
14 or
15 2. file with the application a recent photograph in a format
16 that the Commission specifies; [and]
17 (v) SUBMIT TO THE COMMISSION DOCUMENTATION VERIFYING
18 THAT THE APPLICANT COMPLETED A HUMAN TRAFFICKING AWARENESS TRAINING
19 IN ACCORDANCE WITH § 10–104.2 OF THIS SUBTITLE; AND
20 (VI) apply to the Criminal Justice Information System Central
21 Repository of the Department of Public Safety and Correctional Services for a State
22 criminal history records check as provided in subsection (b) of this section.
