28 (I) (1) RECOGNIZE POTENTIAL VICTIMS OF HUMAN
29 TRAFFICKING;
30 (II) (2) RESPOND TO AN INDIVIDUAL WHO MAY BE OR IS A
31 VICTIM OF HUMAN TRAFFICKING; AND

HOUSE BILL 829 5
1 (III) (3) CONNECT AN INDIVIDUAL WHO MAY BE OR IS A VICTIM
2 OF HUMAN TRAFFICKING WITH AVAILABLE RESOURCES REPORT SUSPECTED
3 INCIDENTS OF HUMAN TRAFFICKING TO APPROPRIATE AUTHORITIES.
4 (B) (C) A LICENSED TAXICAB DRIVER, OR FOR–HIRE DRIVER, OR
5 TRANSPORTATION NETWORK OPERATOR MAY NOT BE HELD CIVILLY OR CRIMINALLY
6 LIABLE FOR REPORTING OR RESPONDING IN GOOD FAITH TO A SUSPECTED
7 INCIDENT OF HUMAN TRAFFICKING.
8 10–106.
9 (a) The term of a for–hire driver’s license is not less than 1 year and not more
10 than 3 years, as the Commission sets.
