23 THIS TITLE.
24 (G) AN APPLICANT FOR THE RENEWAL OF A TRANSPORTATION NETWORK
25 OPERATOR’S LICENSE SHALL SUBMIT TO THE COMMISSION DOCUMENTATION
26 VERIFYING THAT THE APPLICANT COMPLETED A HUMAN TRAFFICKING AWARENESS
27 TRAINING IN ACCORDANCE WITH § 10–104.2 OF THIS TITLE.
28 (G) (1) THIS SUBSECTION DOES NOT APPLY TO AN INDIVIDUAL WHO:
29 (I) SUBMITTED AN APPLICATION FOR A TRANSPORTATION
30 NETWORK OPERATOR’S LICENSE ON OR BEFORE SEPTEMBER 30, 2026; AND

HOUSE BILL 829 7
1 (II) COMPLETED, BETWEEN JULY JUNE 1, 2025, AND
2 SEPTEMBER NOVEMBER 30, 2026, A HUMAN TRAFFICKING AWARENESS TRAINING
3 THAT MEETS THE REQUIREMENTS OF PARAGRAPHS (2) AND (3) OF THIS
4 SUBSECTION.
5 (2) A TRANSPORTATION NETWORK COMPANY MAY NOT ALLOW AN
6 APPLICANT FOR A TRANSPORTATION NETWORK OPERATOR’S LICENSE OR THE
7 HOLDER OF A TEMPORARY OR PERMANENT TRANSPORTATION NETWORK
8 OPERATOR’S LICENSE TO PROVIDE TRANSPORTATION NETWORK SERVICES USING A
9 DIGITAL NETWORK APPLICATION UNLESS THE APPLICANT OR LICENSE HOLDER,
10 WITHIN 30 DAYS AFTER THE APPLICANT OR LICENSE HOLDER FIRST PROVIDES A
11 PREARRANGED RIDE, HAS COMPLETED:
12 (I) THE U.S. DEPARTMENT OF TRANSPORTATION’S LEADERS
13 AGAINST HUMAN TRAFFICKING/COMBATTING TRAFFICKING/COMBATING HUMAN
14 TRAFFICKING IN THE TRANSPORTATION SECTOR AWARENESS TRAINING;
15 (II) ANY NATIONALLY RECOGNIZED HUMAN TRAFFICKING
16 AWARENESS TRAINING PROGRAM; OR
17 (III) ANY DIGITAL TRAINING DEVELOPED BY A TRANSPORTATION
18 NETWORK COMPANY IN CONSULTATION WITH A NATIONALLY RECOGNIZED
19 ORGANIZATION WITH EXPERTISE IN HUMAN TRAFFICKING AWARENESS TRAINING.
20 (3) A HUMAN TRAFFICKING AWARENESS TRAINING THAT AN
21 APPLICANT OR LICENSE HOLDER COMPLETES UNDER PARAGRAPH (2) OF THIS
22 SUBSECTION MUST INCLUDE INFORMATION ON HOW TO:
23 (I) RECOGNIZE POTENTIAL VICTIMS OF HUMAN TRAFFICKING;
24 (II) RESPOND TO AN INDIVIDUAL WHO MAY BE OR IS A VICTIM OF
25 HUMAN TRAFFICKING; AND
26 (III) CONNECT AN INDIVIDUAL WHO MAY BE OR IS A VICTIM
27 REPORT SUSPECTED INCIDENTS OF HUMAN TRAFFICKING WITH AVAILABLE
28 RESOURCES TO APPROPRIATE AUTHORITIES.
29 (4) AN APPLICANT FOR A TRANSPORTATION NETWORK OPERATOR’S
30 LICENSE OR THE HOLDER OF A TEMPORARY OR PERMANENT TRANSPORTATION
31 NETWORK OPERATOR’S LICENSE MAY NOT BE HELD CIVILLY OR CRIMINALLY LIABLE
32 FOR REPORTING OR RESPONDING IN GOOD FAITH TO A SUSPECTED INCIDENT OF
33 HUMAN TRAFFICKING.

